<div class="faq-div">
    <h4 class="mb-3">FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS</h4>
    <div class="w-50 mb-3">
        <p class="faq-question">HOW IS WHEY PROTEIN MADE?</p>
        <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
            <li class="list-group-item">Whey protein begins at the dairy farm with cows producing milk.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">The milk is then refrigerated and shipped to the cheese-makers.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">When the milk arrives at the cheese-making facility, it is quickly heated (pasteurized) to remove any potential pathogens and bacteria.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">From there, it gets introduced to enzymes that separate the whey (liquid) from casein (solids).</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">The casein is then used for cheesemaking and the whey goes to a manufacturing facility.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">There, the liquid whey is filtered to remove the fats and carbs (lactose), becoming whey protein concentrate</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">And finally, the liquid whey concentrate is spray-dried with hot and cold air to become a powder. Then it's bagged and shipped to you!</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

